    "5653076": {
      "title": "Excluding induced subgraphs II: extremal graphs",
      "abstract": "Abstract In this paper we study properties of the classes of graphs not containing a fixed subgraph H as an induced subgraph. In particular, we introduce a new parameter \u03c4(H) and show that fundamental results of extremal graph theory for weak subgraphs carry over to induced subgraphs, if one replaces in the corresponding theorems the chromatic number by \u03c4(H)."
    }
